list.item:
An aircraft shall give way to another aircraft of a class different from
                        its own in the following order: 
                            (a)

mechanically-driven aircraft;
                            (b)

airships;
                            (c)

gliders;
                            (d)

balloons.

div.p:
31. Fuel Requirements. No aircraft shall take off without
                    fuel and oil sufficient, considering the wind and other weather conditions
                    forecast for the flight, at least;
